        { "id": "s3-side-h", "type": "text", "content": "STATIONARY SOLUTIONS", "position": { "x": 610, "y": 250 }, "size": { "w": 290, "h": 14 }, "style": { "fontSize": 10, "color": "#4FC3F7" } },
        { "id": "s3-side-rule", "type": "shape", "shape": "rectangle", "position": { "x": 610, "y": 268 }, "size": { "w": 290, "h": 1 }, "style": { "fill": "#2A3541", "stroke": "#2A3541", "strokeWidth": 0 } },
        { "id": "s3-side-b", "type": "text", "content": "When $\\hat{H}$ is time-independent, the equation separates:\n\n$$ \\hat{H}\\psi_n = E_n \\psi_n $$\n\nThe allowed energies $E_n$ are *eigenvalues*; the $\\psi_n$ are orthonormal eigenstates. This is where discreteness comes from — atoms, bonds, spectral lines.", "position": { "x": 610, "y": 280 }, "size": { "w": 290, "h": 160 }, "style": { "fontSize": 11, "color": "#9DA8B3", "lineHeight": 1.6 } }
